{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584385","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584385"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:45:10+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:45:10+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14464"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14464","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14464"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.13,0.02,0.09,0.74,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7159"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55549"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7159","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7159"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14464"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41089"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"40"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4903"},{"type":"tags","id":"4905"},{"type":"tags","id":"4914"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"17107"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17134"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55549","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/55549"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following blood vessels has the primary function of stretching during systole and recoiling during diastole?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Muscular arteries","Small arteries","Arterioles","Elastic arteries","Veins"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is \u003Cstrong\u003Eelastic arteries\u003C/strong\u003E. Elastic arteries, such as the aorta and its major branches, have a high proportion of elastin in their walls, allowing them to stretch during systole and recoil during diastole. This property, known as the Windkessel effect, helps to maintain blood pressure and flow throughout the cardiac cycle.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMuscular arteries\u003C/strong\u003E have a thicker layer of smooth muscle and less elastin, allowing for vasoconstriction and vasodilation to regulate blood flow to specific organs.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESmall arteries\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Earterioles\u003C/strong\u003E are primarily involved in regulating peripheral resistance and blood flow to tissues through changes in their diameter.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVeins\u003C/strong\u003E have thinner walls and larger lumens compared to arteries, serving mainly as capacitance vessels for blood storage and return to the heart.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe elastic recoil of large arteries is crucial for:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EConverting pulsatile flow from the heart into continuous flow in peripheral vessels\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EMaintaining diastolic blood pressure\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EReducing cardiac afterload\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EProtecting smaller vessels from damage due to pressure fluctuations\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Elastic arteries, such as the aorta and its major branches, stretch during systole and recoil during diastole to maintain blood pressure and flow.","This elastic property of large arteries helps to convert pulsatile flow from the heart into continuous flow in peripheral vessels."],"references":["Hemmings, H. C., \u0026 Egan, T. D. Pharmacology and physiology for anesthesia e-book: foundations and clinical application. 2012. Elsevier Health Sciences","Tucker WD, Arora Y, Mahajan K. Anatomy, Blood Vessels. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29262226.","Messas E, Pernot M, Couade M. Arterial wall elasticity: state of the art and future prospects. Diagn Interv Imaging. 2013 May;94(5):561-9. doi: 10.1016/j.diii.2013.01.025. Epub 2013 Apr 22. PMID: 23619291."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41089"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14464"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41089","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/41089"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-10-16T18:15:14+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-16T18:15:52+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7159"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55549"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"40","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/40"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\u2699\ufe0f","name":"Physiology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"4"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCou